ENTRY            M0105   20260413   20260518   20260518       M145
SUBENT        M0105001   20260413   20260518   20260518       M145
BIB                 10         19
TITLE      Photoprotons from Li-6.
AUTHOR     (E.D.Makhnovskii)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSFTI)
REFERENCE  (J,JET,19,769,1964)
            English translation of J,ZET,46,1136,1964.
           (J,ZET,46,1136,1964)
FACILITY   (SYNCH,4RUSFTI)
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
SAMPLE     The target (90% 6Li and 10% 7Li) had thickness 0f 6.8
            mg/sm**2.
METHOD     (EXTB,SITA)
DETECTOR   (PLATE)
HISTORY    (19840405C)
           (19910202A) Corrected by V.Varlamov, V.Mclane.
           (20130530A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: dates,
            REFERENCE, REACTION, STATUS, lowercase.
           (20260413A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: AUTHOR,
            REFERENCE, SAMPLE, PART-DET, ANALYSIS, ERR-ANALYS,
            COMMENT, DATA, COMMON, STATUS.
ENDBIB              19
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           22
SUBENT        M0105002   20260413   20260518   20260518       M145
BIB                  5         12
REACTION   (3-LI-6(G,P)2-HE-5,,DA/DE,,BRA/REL)
ANALYSIS    Energy and angular distributions of protons
             produced by irradiation of 6Li with
             Bremsstrahlung of maximum energy En-max = 20 MeV
             were measured in nuclear emulsions at angles 20,
             50, 70, 90, 110, 130, and 160 degrees.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical errors.
STATUS     (CURVE,,E.D.Makhnovskii,J,JET,19,769,1964)
            Data from Fig. 1.
HISTORY    (20130530A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: BRS -> BRA.
           (20260413A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: ANALYSIS,
            ERR-ANALYS, COMMON, DATA, STATUS.
ENDBIB              12
COMMON               3          3
EN-MAX     ANG-MIN    ANG-MAX
MEV        ADEG       ADEG
    20.         20.      160.
